The Android Stagefright exploit targets a media processing bug in many Android devices, allowing attackers to remotely run harmful code by sending a specially crafted video or multimedia message. It affects devices running older Android versions, especially before 2016, potentially giving control without user interaction. This shows how vulnerabilities in media handling can expose devices even before users open files. Terms like “remote code execution,” “media parsing flaws,” and “Android security patches” help understand how such exploits work and why strong device updates and secure messaging can better protect data.